### Secure Notes API — quick tests
### Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension.
### Click "Send Request" above each block.

@host = http://localhost:3000
@email = ada@example.com
@password = correct horse battery staple

### Health
GET {{host}}/health

### Register
POST {{host}}/auth/register
content-type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Ada"
}

### Login
# @name login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
content-type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.refreshToken}}

### Me
GET {{host}}/me
authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Create note
# @name newNote
POST {{host}}/notes
authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "title": "First note",
  "body": "Hello, secure world."
}

### List my notes
GET {{host}}/notes
authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Get one
GET {{host}}/notes/{{newNote.response.body.id}}
authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Rotate refresh
POST {{host}}/auth/refresh
content-type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }

### Logout
POST {{host}}/auth/logout
content-type: application/json

{ "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}" }

### Admin: users (needs admin role — promote a user via `npx prisma studio`)
GET {{host}}/admin/users
authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Google Sign-In (only if GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID/SECRET set in .env)
# Open in a browser instead of REST Client:
# http://localhost:3000/auth/google/start
